name: Babi Guling Sunari

review 2: We hired a driver to have a tour in singaraja and we ask if we can have babi guling for lunch. He took us here in a local warung the food was good and busy little warung but bit disappointed with the driver because he was already paid for driving us there and charged us 3x the price for lunch. The normal price is rp25,000 he charged us rp65,000 each. So be careful to some doggy people will do anything to screw you over. He kept explaining karma. Well lets see if he is looked after by being a petty crook.

review 4:
One of the best Nasi Lawar or Nasi Be Guling in Buleleng.
Recommended to come at 9:45 - 10:30 am
Very crowded everyday
review 5: This is the best plaxe for eating Balinese Suckling Pig (Babi Guling) in Singaraja. They have large parking space and the price for a portion with extra crispy pork crisp is very reasonable.
